[3] Cholera - Ukraine (Donetsk)
Date: Mon 11 Jul 2011
Source: Ukrainian News Agency [edited]
http://un.ua/eng/article/338689.html


The Donetsk regional sanitary and epidemiological station has
confirmed other 2 cases of cholera in Mariupol, Donetsk region, the
sanitary and epidemiological station said. According to the report, 19
ill people and 9 who were asymptomatic have been discharged from
hospitals. 3 patients are still undergoing treatment and the state of
their health is stable.

As Ukrainian News earlier reported, from 29 May 2011 to 4 Jul 2011,
Mariupol doctors registered 20 cases of illness in cholera.

